<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Killbomb</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Avault gives it 3 1/2 stars out of 5. The review is intelligently written and brings up some valid gripes. Definitely worth a read. I have to disagree somewhat with him about the voice acting though. While some is bad, I particularly enjoyed the voice of the male warrior. Anyone know who the voice actor is? <A HREF="http://www.avault.com/reviews/review_temp.asp?game=divi" TARGET=_blank>http://www.avault.com/reviews/review_temp.asp?game=divi</A> </FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">lost soul</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">well first off any site that would give diablo 1 a 5/5 score and this game a 3.5/5 is deffinetly out of whack with reality anyways.So i take there review with a grain of salt.Another thing that really frustrates me is when people compare this to diablo 2,yes the interface looks somehwhat like Diablo 2 but this game is on a totally grander scale.Diablo 2 is so dang linear its not even funny.Divine divinity you can do what u want when u want,can u say that about diablo 2??? nope. divine divinity you have so many sidequests it will make ur head spin can you say that about diablo 2??? nope.In Divine divinity when you pick a class can you cross over and specialize in another class skill?? yes   can you do that in Diablo 2?? nope.Its to bad that people want to pass this off as a diablo clone because its not at all.This game has so much replay value its scary and i think reviewers forget to mention that.<BR>I also have seen reviews where people take points off for a lack of a multiplayer when it never claimed to have one in the first place.thats just like a reviewer taking points off for a game like Ever quest because it doesnt have a single player,how can they do that??? My advice to you people is if you want to see the most honest scoring for games go to pc game review.com.Hundreds of players like you and i rate games and whatever it averages out to is usually a good indication of how good a game is.i tend to not listen to the so called proffesional reviewers because all to often there wrong.i would rather take the opinion of 100 people then 1.<BR>Prime example most pro reviwers were saying diablo was a game of the likes never seen before and everyone should get it,heck i was seeing people giving it a 100/100.so then i bought it and omg what a pile of junk.At pc game website where us normal players review games its about 92/100 and it deserves to be that high/</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Styks</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well i tend to agree with this review, even if I would have given a better mark.<P>Actually, even if diablo 1 has a 5/5 score, it should be consider as a "character focused" action-rpg game. So in this particular kind of games, it's actually a very good game and his mark doesn't surprise me.<P>Divine divinity is different, as it wants to be a diablo-like gameplay with a story, interesting NPC, nice quests and so on. So in this kind of game, well it have some lacks and they highlighted them. We can't blame them for thinking that this game has some lacks and should be better in some ways...<P>Styks</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Styks</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Concerning the multiplayer aspect, I totally agree with you. The lack of multiplayer should definitely NOT be a reason to lower the mark, as this game was NEVER intended to be multiplayer.<P>Styks</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">blood</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This review of DD is actually one of the better ones I've read. I disagree with some aspects of the review but that's irrelevant. To question how Diablo 1 got 5/5 and DD got 3.5/5 is simply juvenile. Before Diablo 1 came out, was there any other RPG remotely similar that offered that kind of mindless-clicking, frantic gameplay? Diablo 1 MADE the action-RPG genre. And I seriously doubt you'd find *ANY* review, be it from "pros" or regular gamers, that considered the original Diablo "average" or even merely "good". Maybe you're just a Diablo-hater, and that's fine or perhaps you're just a DD-lover, and that's fine too, but whether you're willing to admit it or not, at least 75% of DD, from start to finish, IS hack-n-slash. I wonder why they'd find something like that diabolically fun. The fact that you'd even bring Diablo 1 up is testament to how popular and well-received the game was. I seriously doubt gamers would be talking about DD three, four or five years from now.<P><p>[This message has been edited by blood (edited 22-10-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Huckman</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Totally agree with that point.<P>If you wanted a game to be multiplayer but it's not- don't make it take the hit in the review score.  If the game was MARKETED as a multiplayer game and is not, then slice it and dice it.<P>Many casual readers of publications (both print and online) glance over a review score to see if the game is worth their time.  If the review is overtly positive or negative, they will often times dig a little bit deeper.  A review of 3.5/5 says to most people: "It's OK, but not good.  Don't bother unless you have a lot of time/money on your hands". <P>CODICIL:  I don't agree with this line of reasoning and think that reviews should be read in their entirety (after all, reviewers are human and humans are inconsistent).  I would LOVE for Larian to make some beaucoup bucks on this game and wish that reviewers would instill confidence to the reader in the SCORE that is often reflected in the TEXT for those shallower readers of the literature.<BR><P>------------------<BR>"25 cents is a good price for 2 elephants, but only if you have 25 cents and only if you need 2 elephants."<BR>- Woodrow Wilson</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Spam</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, I thought that was a very fair review, with plenty of good points,  even though personally I think it deserved a higher rating.<P>I'd just like to point out though - everybody who is complaining that it was marked down for not having multiplayer - <I>where exactly</I> does it say that?  All the review does is point out that there is no Multiplayer - a fair point which is pretty much vital in any review nowadays as many people buy games solely based on that aspect.<P>[This message has been edited by Spam (edited 22-10-2002).]<p>[This message has been edited by Spam (edited 22-10-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Spam</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">And if you want proof of that point - do the math!<P>7 categories:<BR>Graphics<BR>Interface<BR>Gameplay<BR>Multiplayer<BR>Sound FX<BR>Music<BR>Intelligence and Difficulty<P>Max score of 5 stars for each category, for a Max Total of 35<P>Now if they counted multiplayer as a Zero score, the total for DD was 19.5, giving an average of 19.5/7 = 2.8<BR>However if you dont count the multiplayer category at all (since it doesn't apply to the game, duh!) you get 19.5/6 = 3.25 - which they've obviously rounded up to 3.5 stars!<P>SO QUIT YER MOANING!!</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Huckman</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Good points, Spam.<P>I kind of got off track from the original post and was discussing many of the other reviews of the game (PC Gamer, for one) who detracted from the score for lack of multiplay. <P>BTW, the review at AVault is very professionally written with very good support to his points.  I will start reading AVault more often, as I grow weary of the really boring RPG guy at gamespot.  <BR> <P>------------------<BR>"25 cents is a good price for 2 elephants, but only if you have 25 cents and only if you need 2 elephants."<BR>- Woodrow Wilson</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Killbomb</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">For the record, different people wrote the DD and Diablo 1 reviews. You also can't judge the quality of the site from one review (even though I personally think the DD review was well done). Avault is not the fastest to get reviews out but they are usually thorough and well written.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">lost soul</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Spam i wasnt saying that review in particular but there are reviewers that take points off for multiplayer and thats not right period.<P>I agree with huck it doesnnt matter what the guy or girl writes in the review,most people will just look at a score and if they see a 3.5/5,more then likely that person is thinking this is a been here done that type of game im not interested,so they wont read the review.<BR>i dont care how well the review is written 3.5/5 =  70/100 thats entirely to low,ya we all have opinions but i just cant see how 3.5/5 is represenetive of how much was really put in this game.guarentee you if Divine Divinity said made by blizzard on the box the game would have scored higher.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
